                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d958">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/3016.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of War</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">War Department</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 4, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Brigadier General Duncan, commanding Department
                    Texas, telegraphs from Fort Sam Houston, Tex., March 4, the following: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>From Colonel Steever:</p>
                        <p>“Fighting in Chihuahua began this morning. Villa, loyal to Madero,
                            attacked Orozco, who quit Madero 1st instant. Salazar, appealed to by
                            Orozco, is entraining men to go south to Orozco’s assistance. Probably
                            over 4,000 rebels in Juarez, largely mounted. Additions daily. More
                            disorder in Juarez not improbable.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">H. L. Stimson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
